# rize-backend environment variables
#
# Copy this to .env for local development:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Every variable below is read by internal/config (internal/config/config.go).
# Anything left unset falls back to its documented default, which is fine for
# local development but must be set explicitly in any deployed environment —
# see docs/deployment.md for how integration/production populate these via
# GitHub Actions secrets/variables and Secret Manager.
#
# This file is kept in sync with internal/config by
# internal/config/env_example_test.go: that test fails if config.Load reads
# a variable this file doesn't document.

# ── Server ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# TCP port the HTTP server listens on.
# Default: 8080
PORT=8080

# Deployment environment: one of development, staging, production.
# Gates the CORS wildcard check below — only "development" may resolve to a
# wildcard CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS.
# Default: development
ENVIRONMENT=development

# ── Database ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# PostgreSQL/TimescaleDB connection string. May be left empty in local
# scaffolding contexts (e.g. running the binary without a database);
# /readyz reports "not_configured" in that case. The value below matches
# the credentials docker-compose.yml provisions for the local db service.
# Default: (empty)
DATABASE_URL=postgres://rize:rize@localhost:5432/rize?sslmode=disable

# ── Auth ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# PEM-encoded RSA private key (PKCS#1 or PKCS#8, RSA-2048 minimum) used to
# sign and verify access tokens — see documentation/security.md §Token
# model. In development, if left unset, the backend falls back to an
# ephemeral in-memory key (invalidated on every restart); never rely on
# that fallback outside development. Do NOT put a real signing key in this
# file or commit a real key to version control.
# Generate one with: openssl genrsa -out jwt-signing-key.pem 2048
# Default: (empty — ephemeral key used only in development)
# Leave unset in development for an ephemeral in-memory key.
# Generate a real one with: openssl genrsa -out jwt-signing-key.pem 2048
# JWT_SIGNING_KEY=

# ── Brute-force login lockout (RIZ-59) ─────────────────────────────────

# Number of consecutive failed login attempts against a single account
# that triggers a lockout, independent of per-IP rate limiting — see
# documentation/security.md §API hardening ("brute-force lockout on
# login").
# Default: 10
AUTH_LOCKOUT_THRESHOLD=10

# Lockout duration applied the first time an account is locked. Each
# subsequent lockout on the same account doubles the previous duration,
# capped at AUTH_LOCKOUT_MAX_DURATION. Accepts a Go duration string
# (e.g. 15m, 1h).
# Default: 15m
AUTH_LOCKOUT_BASE_DURATION=15m

# Ceiling the doubling lockout duration is capped at. Accepts a Go
# duration string (e.g. 24h).
# Default: 24h
AUTH_LOCKOUT_MAX_DURATION=24h

# ── CORS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Comma-separated list of origins allowed to make cross-origin requests.
# Per documentation/security.md §API hardening, this must never resolve to
# "*" outside ENVIRONMENT=development — Load fails fast if it does.
# Default: * (development only)
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=*

# ── Rate limiting ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Per-IP request budget enforced by the rate-limit middleware, in
# requests/minute.
# Default: 100
RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS_PER_MINUTE=100

# ── Timeouts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# How long graceful shutdown waits for in-flight requests to finish, in
# seconds.
# Default: 10
SHUTDOWN_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=10

# ── Sync changelog retention (RIZ-72) ──────────────────────────────────

# How old a sync_changelog row (by its created_at) must be before the
# in-process retention pruner considers it eligible for deletion, in hours.
# 2160 (90 days) comfortably bounds the commit-ordered pull cursor's xid8
# wraparound-safety window (migrations 000024/000025) while giving a
# long-dormant device's stale cursor a generous grace period before its
# next pull is forced into a full re-pull.
# Default: 2160
SYNC_CHANGELOG_MAX_AGE=2160

# How often (in seconds) the in-process retention pruner wakes up to delete
# another batch of aged-out sync_changelog rows.
# Default: 3600
SYNC_CHANGELOG_PRUNE_INTERVAL_SECONDS=3600

# Maximum number of sync_changelog rows deleted per prune tick.
# Default: 5000
SYNC_CHANGELOG_PRUNE_BATCH_SIZE=5000

# ── Observability ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# SENTRY_DSN is not read by internal/config yet — Sentry integration is
# tracked by RIZ-53 and not implemented. Left here, commented out, so this
# file only needs a value filled in (not a new entry added) once RIZ-53
# lands.
# SENTRY_DSN=  # added by RIZ-53 (not yet implemented)
